) (
<figureCitation id="46D916B7BAA5120DCB1F303AD70D7018" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Guzmania panamensis. A Habit in Santa Fe National Park (province of Veraguas, Panama) B Inflorescence, bracts and flowers C Drawing of the flower parts: C 1 Floral bract, C 2 Sepal, C 3 Petals with filaments and anthers, C 4 Pistil. All from D. A. Caceres Gonzalez 4385. Photographs and drawing by Daniel A. Caceres G." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10845" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). It was observed flowering in December (start of the dry season).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="83FE0A1FCE9761FF342F94F700C73FC0" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="944F3B2B5192E50225B20D0F9958B421" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4E685BB0377ACA297C694A9C21429B8" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="F9D8D274A07A7D80AF4DA8340911EE02" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="6BC7DB40126EA3C1C487056B361B9ADA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honour of Panama country.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6A5FE625EB34626439E763A06C79BFD4" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="6B61C798782C8F1645C786170F0E04BF" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55E37475B098EF89B00E1347565F6147" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="5E7ED236414B20632E8F1F4347BC10F4" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="28EC8A6382DEBF879AE330950FD3E64D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected only once in Panama. In the type locality area, only three individuals were observed and hence it is assumed to be uncommon. No other specimen could be found among the material that has been collected for seventy years, as part of the project Flora of Panama of the Missouri Botanical Garden, supporting the view that this taxon is rare even inside this national park. Similar habitats, surrounding the park have been visited by the author and no specimen similar to 
<taxonomicName id="32B8082F6AE1CDD19A0891F638CD9B30" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="FB229CE3631CE1DED6892D3794C5E7D6" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found in such areas. Therefore, in the conservation assessment presented here (following 
<bibRefCitation id="F161AFAFE813B5B37DD7EF2C28EFC1FB" author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="B3" refString="IUCN, , 2001. IUCN Red List categories and criteria. Version 3.1. First edition, Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge, United Kingdom." title="IUCN Red List categories and criteria. Version 3.1. First edition, Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge, United Kingdom." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
guidelines), 
<taxonomicName id="22D987325F4CCA1A3219702D5834C778" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="0F51C8CBDE0556E68523B94711CF3B7F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is categorized as Critically Endangered (CR), represented by only a single distribution record and based on the criterium B2biii.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="964D95A59466311A0543FBECF1286744" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" type="observations">
<paragraph id="48E7EABECFA11EF33A2CCACCDA3920AC" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBF9696E2ED1C78CDF8FC2F803E1AEAE" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">
Four species have a close resemblance with 
<taxonomicName id="5F0D4962D5B9E43DC5F9DA4EC87CCAD3" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="7A2910F05FA12A5CC24FE192EEA2FAC0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="F2FC3C96329C8AF819390AE032D697DF" authorityName="Rusby ex Mez" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="monostachia">
<emphasis id="08838D6A19186C6AC0FEE921D17C8C10" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania monostachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Rusby 
<emphasis id="21A5A7E31884D15FF8E2772ABF6B30B5" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">ex</emphasis>
Mez, 
<taxonomicName id="0AEA6600CC0953BD6231A7064068514D" authorityName="Mez" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Schult. &amp; Schult. f." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="berteroniana">
<emphasis id="84A26F8C232C78187FB937FC8B3AD374" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania berteroniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schult. &amp; Schult. f.) Mez, 
<taxonomicName id="103C8E514CD00964F62F1A0774501CA5" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="elvallensis">
<emphasis id="CFE2334F72A8BFF908E137A3B05EF1E0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania elvallensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Luther, and 
<taxonomicName id="6E8043C1C33062BC18A762544FF719A8" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="skotakii">
<emphasis id="FCA586DFE2EB6E32B42351CE8C011D07" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Guzmania skotakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Luther.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC4ED1FB484081025473D25A866E0E49" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="76173F12847C30A0D178E4E2FF7E4B7F" authorityName="Rusby ex Mez" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="monostachia">
<emphasis id="10CABFD2D92A3F6AF5CE223879AFD615" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<pageBreakToken id="5FEABA90C697294FABCA320EFF6FA7EC" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" start="start">Guzmania</pageBreakToken>
monostachia
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="632E2B9BA176CA82913BD1DE087BAD51" author="Smith, LB" journalOrPublisher="Bromelia" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refId="B8" refString="Smith, LB, Downs, RJ, 1977. Tillandsioideae (Bromeliaceae). Flora Neotropica. Monograph 14 (2). Hafner Press, New York." title="Tillandsioideae (Bromeliaceae). Flora Neotropica. Monograph 14 (2). Hafner Press, New York." year="1977">Smith and Downs 1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9D50CB254661112B2A66B9564AFE55E0" author="Mez, C" journalOrPublisher="Bromelia" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refId="B7" refString="Mez, C, 1896. Bromeliaceae. In: De Candolle ALPP, De Candolle ACP (Ed) MonographiaePhanerogamarum9: 658-881. Sumptibus Masson &amp; Cie., Paris." title="Bromeliaceae. In: De Candolle ALPP, De Candolle ACP (Ed) MonographiaePhanerogamarum 9: 658 - 881. Sumptibus Masson &amp; Cie., Paris." year="1896">Mez 1896</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1460F73C106CC3CF1425DF31B957F659" author="Utley, JF" journalOrPublisher="In: Davidse G, Sousa SM, Chater AO (Eds) Flora Mesoamericana" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="89 - 156" refId="B9" refString="Utley, JF, 1994. Bromeliaceae. In: Davidse G, Sousa SM, Chater AO (Eds) Flora Mesoamericana 6: 89 - 156" title="Bromeliaceae." volume="6" year="1994">Utley 1994</bibRefCitation>
), but differs from it by its larger size of the plant and the color of the floral bracts. 
<taxonomicName id="06AFAC63F61111F36E89352314793203" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="009DB6B8909628DDC9E1EC0FF9D6E933" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when flowering reaches about 67 cm tall vs. 20-40 cm in 
<taxonomicName id="8A505206D5FC23DB4635C2BE8637156F" authorityName="Rusby ex Mez" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="monostachia">
<emphasis id="26F72D34C9E058F322BF87A8628C1030" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania monostachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The peduncle of the new species is much longer than the leaves with red floral bracts and yellow flowers; while in 
<taxonomicName id="6199C700D410579B5D3A6ED89E3DB519" authorityName="Rusby ex Mez" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="monostachia">
<emphasis id="59802237185D52ADD9886F5FB64AD15A" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania monostachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the peduncle is much shorter, the floral bracts are bright red or rarely white, and the flowers are usually white with conspicuous brown longitudinal stripes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2993DB343B9B287F185F4497C6C4ECD9" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
In 
<taxonomicName id="4761A33B9BC4FDC795E4410685F01D26" authorityName="Mez" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Schult. &amp; Schult. f." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="berteroniana">
<emphasis id="D08955310853C1D91632D15FCC31C007" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania berteroniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the floral bracts exceed the sepals, and the sepals are 22 mm long (connate for 2 mm); while in 
<taxonomicName id="3998532613235DB332B4F63D20F2032E" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="5F99E5329BF0C056A98831B7F985B778" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the floral bracts are shorter than the flowers (including the sepals), and the sepals are 25 mm long (connate for 6-7 mm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="328E8D55FF9B41E8030B912775C908C6" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
This new species differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName id="2097525D875A8A2603900ED220CEA929" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="elvallensis">
<emphasis id="3CF5EA27434D953CC3FE038228C39C36" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania elvallensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8940FF0AB017CA5307EAAE5842DDC78B" author="Luther, HE" journalOrPublisher="Bromelia" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="8 - 12" refId="B5" refString="Luther, HE, 1996. A new Guzmania species from central Panama. Bromelia 3: 8 - 12" title="A new Guzmania species from central Panama." volume="3" year="1996">Luther 1996</bibRefCitation>
), by the color of its petals (yellow vs. pale green). Another important feature is that in 
<taxonomicName id="DC75056FF97DF0D9ABBEEC5A7D471485" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="F0189D6F0AEF87CEF8859221F55B44FE" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the floral bracts are red, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="249E4E0DAFD2825CCB289511F866DF51" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="elvallensis">
<emphasis id="C0AA8FBC259636DBFBC0DA1F74D81E8A" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania elvallensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are green.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38B26E096BC967BB47A6B9F289F6EFD9" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName id="D53B1F7E748F8B701E7A97E25010469E" authorityName="Caceres Gonzalez" authorityYear="2013" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="8A93E6615342680878E3EB68767EB505" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName id="4150A8E0F908C33E1578BB0955EBDF70" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="skotakii">
<emphasis id="1A4397397047C4FFD9BFAD9E0314259C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guzmania skotakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6483206B5541C3308353ED2A1741D3FB" author="Luther, HE" journalOrPublisher="Selbyana" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="68 - 90" refId="B4" refString="Luther, HE, 1991. Miscellaneous new taxa of Bromeliaceae (VIII). Selbyana 12: 68 - 90" title="Miscellaneous new taxa of Bromeliaceae (VIII)." volume="12" year="1991">Luther 1991</bibRefCitation>
), by its smaller leaves, chartaceous in open rosette with sheaths ovate-elliptic (9-11 
<normalizedToken id="1A9F6E69D1E57D93EBAA565E4DB5784A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 cm) vs. longer leaves, coriaceous and erect, with sheaths broadly elliptic (20 
<normalizedToken id="23B2A6B2EFDB6CAD91F2147B8D222E29" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10 cm). In the first species the floral bracts are obovate, acuminate 2-2.2 
<normalizedToken id="D6A82E552752E4A921A124B34283F507" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.9-2 cm, shorter than the sepals, with yellow petals; whereas in the second species the floral bracts are elliptic to oblanceolate, obtuse to subacute 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="5CA6800EFEE7854151A97F5C6DDF0A8B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.6-2.5 cm, longer than the sepals, with cream petals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
